    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-18T17:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-18T17:40:00-05:00" n="354"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d354">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1616.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargá <persName type="from">White</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-18T18:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 18, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram of November 14, 10 p.m. Popular vote Jiménez 40,076; Vasquez Vidal
                    39,632; votes electoral college Jiménez 300 out of 632. For Jiménez seven
                    provinces out of twelve; Senators 7; Deputies 14. [Báez] has often expressed his
                    satisfaction with elections and while he is surrounded by people who are urging
                    him to stay in power will resign if United States takes firm stand. Have secured
                    signed confidential letter from Jiménez, Velásquez thoroughly satisfactory as to
                    financial control.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
